 Algerian Football Federation Logo
The Algerian Football Federation is the governing body of football in Algeria. It was formed in 1962 and was based in the capital Algiers. It has jurisdiction on the Algerian football league system and is in charge of the men’s and women’s national teams. Although an unofficial national team had played fixtures since 1958, the first recognized international took place in January 1963, some six months after independence. In 2021, twenty structures were added to the Algerian Football Federation.

Cevital Logo Cevital is the largest private conglomerate in Algeria, with interests in the agri-food sector, retail, industry and services, created by Issad Rebrab. The company’s headquarters are in Béjaïa, Algeria. Cevital is a founding member of the Desertec project. The company’s earnings in 2009 were US$3,589 million. Source
